                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7071: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Legation in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-18T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 18, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>168. I understand that Executive Yuan this morning approved appointment of Chin
                    Teh-chun, member of Chahar Provincial Government, to be chairman thereof in
                    place of Sung Cheh-yuan. Chin is said to be acceptable to Japanese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
